      "summary": "Discovery is not the creation of new knowledge but the revelation of pre-existing constraints. The structure was always there; what changes is the observer's ability to perceive it. This reframing dissolves the mystery of discovery: the question shifts from 'how do minds create truth?' to 'what conditions enable constraint perception?' A constraint becomes visible when the observer's representational framework develops sufficient resolution in the relevant dimensions. Every major scientific discovery can be recast as the moment a hidden constraint became perceptible.",
