    "id": "dtu_447_exploration_vs_preservation_tradeoff",
    "tier": "core",
    "tags": [
      "stsvk_447",
      "exploration",
      "vs",
      "preservation",
      "tradeoff"
    ],
    "human": {
      "summary": "The exploration-preservation tradeoff captures the fundamental tension between seeking new knowledge or states and protecting existing valuable configurations, a tension that intensifies as a system accumulates more worth preserving.",
      "bullets": [
        "Every exploratory action risks destabilizing existing valuable states, creating an irreducible tension with preservation.",
        "As a system accumulates more valuable structure, the cost of failed exploration increases superlinearly.",
        "Optimal strategies shift from exploration-heavy to preservation-heavy as accumulated value grows."
      ]
    },
    "core": {
      "definitions": [
        {
          "term": "Exploration Cost",
          "definition": "The expected value of existing structure placed at risk when an intelligent system probes unknown regions of its state space."
        },
        {
          "term": "Preservation Burden",
          "definition": "The ongoing resource expenditure required to maintain existing valuable configurations against entropy and perturbation."
        }
      ],
      "invariants": [
        "No system can simultaneously maximize exploration and preservation; resources allocated to one are unavailable for the other.",
        "The optimal exploration rate decreases as the ratio of accumulated value to remaining discoverable value increases.",
        "Any system that never explores will eventually be destroyed by environmental changes it failed to anticipate."
      ],
      "claims": [
        "Biological aging may be an evolved solution to the exploration-preservation tradeoff, clearing old structures to enable new adaptation.",
        "Civilizations that over-index on preservation become brittle; those that over-index on exploration become chaotic.",
        "The exploration-preservation tradeoff is a generalization of the explore-exploit tradeoff that accounts for the fragility of existing value."
      ],
      "examples": [
        "NASA's Mars rover missions exemplify the exploration-preservation tradeoff: each drive command risks the irreplaceable rover on unknown terrain, and mission planners increasingly favor conservative traversal as the rover accumulates more scientific value in its instruments and data.",
        "The European Union's precautionary principle in biotechnology regulation embodies a preservation-heavy stance, accepting slower innovation in exchange for protecting existing agricultural ecosystems and food safety from poorly understood risks of genetic modification."
      ],
      "nextActions": [
        "Explore dtu_443 for fast intelligence risks, dtu_449 for intelligence without expansion"
      ]
    },
    "machine": {
      "kind": "formal_model",
      "math": {
        "space": "X = (V_acc, V_disc, R) where V_acc is accumulated value, V_disc is discoverable remaining value, R is risk per exploration step measured as P(destroying fraction of V_acc)",
        "variables": {
          "x": "state",
          "u": "control",
          "w": "noise",
          "θ": "parameters"
        },
        "dynamics": "V_acc(t+1) = (1-R·α_t)·V_acc(t) + α_t·E[discovery]; V_disc(t+1) = V_disc(t) - α_t·E[discovery] where α_t ∈ [0,1] is exploration intensity at time t",
        "constraints": [
          "V_acc(t) ≥ V_min for all t: accumulated value must never drop below minimum viability threshold",
          "α_t · R · V_acc(t) ≤ B_risk: expected value at risk per step bounded by risk budget B_risk"
        ],
        "potential": "V(α, V_acc, V_disc) = R·α·V_acc - α·E[discovery]·(V_disc/V_total) ≥ 0 when V_acc >> V_disc, forcing preservation dominance as value accumulates",
        "implication": "Optimal exploration rate α*(t) = B_risk / (R · V_acc(t)), which decreases as accumulated value grows, producing a natural transition from exploration-dominant to preservation-dominant regimes"
      },
      "primaryFormula": "α*(t) = min(1, B_risk / (R · V_acc(t))) · (V_disc(t) / V_total), showing optimal exploration decays with accumulated value and remaining discovery potential"
    },
